Input:
    Cleaned rice-domain corpus C = {c1, c2, ..., cn}
    Entity schema S_e
    Relation schema S_r
    Domain dictionary Dict
    Confidence threshold θ

Output:
    Rice knowledge graph G = (V, E)
    Evidence mapping table T_map

1. Initialize node set V as an empty set
2. Initialize edge set E as an empty set
3. Initialize evidence mapping table T_map as an empty table

4. Define entity types in S_e:
       rice variety, parent material, agronomic trait, disease,
       pest, pathogen, symptom, control measure, cultivation measure,
       growth stage, suitable region, environmental factor, and yield trait

5. Define relation types in S_r:
       has_trait, suitable_for, resistant_to, caused_by, has_symptom,
       damages_part, controlled_by, applied_at_stage, requires_condition,
       related_to_region, and supported_by_document

6. For each text chunk c_i in C do

7.     Perform domain term matching using Dict
           Identify known rice varieties, disease names, pest names,
           growth stages, regions, and management terms

8.     Extract candidate entities from c_i according to S_e

9.     Normalize entity names:
           Merge aliases, remove redundant modifiers,
           unify Chinese and English expressions when necessary,
           and map abbreviations to standard names

10.    Extract candidate relations from c_i according to S_r
           Use rule-based patterns, dependency cues, or model-based extraction

11.    For each candidate entity e do

12.        If e is valid and belongs to the predefined entity schema then
13.            Add e to node set V
14.            Link e with supporting chunk c_i in T_map
15.        End If

16.    End For

17.    For each candidate relation r = <head, relation, tail> do

18.        Check whether head and tail are valid domain entities

19.        Check whether relation type belongs to S_r

20.        Estimate confidence score score(r)

21.        If score(r) >= θ then
22.            Add triple <head, relation, tail> to edge set E
23.            Record supporting chunk id of r in T_map
24.        End If

25.    End For

26. End For

27. Perform graph post-processing:
       Remove isolated noisy nodes,
       merge duplicated nodes,
       remove conflicting low-confidence edges,
       and retain evidence links for each node and relation

28. Construct graph G = (V, E)

29. Save G and T_map to graph storage

30. Return G and T_map
